### Subagents

| Action | Tool | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| Invoke a subagent | `subagent_invoke({ role, prompt, context_files, commands })` | role: Coder/Tester/Reviewer |

**When to use subagents:**
- **2+ independent tasks** — Parallel work on non-overlapping files
- **Code + tests + docs** — Split into separate stages with `depends_on`
- **Complex refactoring** — Delegate one layer per subagent

**When NOT to use subagents:**
- Single file edit (< 50 LoC change)
- Sequential dependency chain (read → analyze → decide next)
- Pure research/question (no file modification)

**Input format:**
```javascript
subagent_invoke({
  role: "Coder",                    // Coder | Tester | Reviewer
  prompt: "Implement X feature...", // Detailed instructions
  context_files: ["src/x.ts"],      // Files subagent can read
  commands: ["npm run build"],      // Shell commands to execute
  wait: true                        // Block until complete (default: false)
})
```

